all calls (internal/external) can be transferred to all destinations.

enum unsp__KeysetOperationMode

The Keyset Operation feature allows lines on a keyset device to be DeviceBased or LineBased.

DeviceBased means that the data of the Keyset Primary Line is used for call origination and features that require that data and LineBased means that the data of this individual line is used for those purposes. The Keyset Operation Modes can vary on a per line, per device basis. That is, a BGL that has an appearance on more than one device may be LineBased on one and DeviceBased on another, and operation modes may be different depending on whether the secondary line is the originating or terminating side of a call. If not specified, the default value is DeviceBased.

Enumerator
DeviceBased 

Device Based.

LineBased 

Line Based.

enum unsp__SRType

Station Restriction Type.

Enumerator
NoRestriction 

No Restrictions.

SemiRestrictedLine 

Originating: Semi-Restricted Originating (SRO) - The line cannot make a call outside of the BG, but can call the attendant or another line within the BG that is not restricted, who can make a call to an outside line for them Terminating: Semi-Restricted Terminating (SRT) - The line cannot receive a call from outside of the BG, but can receive calls from an attendant or another line within the BG that is not restricted, including a call from outside of the BG.

FullyRestrictedLine 

Originating: Fully-Restricted Originating(FRO) - In addition to the SRO restrictions, the line cannot make a call outside of the BG, nor can the line dial the attendant, nor can the line be forwarded or transferred out of the BG Terminating: Fully-Restricted Terminating (FRT) - In addition to the SRT restrictions, the line cannot receive a call from outside of the BG, nor receive a call from the attendant, nor can it receive a call being forwarded or transferred from outside of the BG.

FullyRestrictedWithAttendant 

Originating: Fully-Restricted Originating with Attendant (FRO-A) - FRO-A is the same as FRO, other than the Attendant can be called and can transfer to other lines within the same BG Terminating: Fully-Restricted Terminating with Attendant (FRT-A) - FRT-A is the same as FRT, other than calls from the Attendant can be received (as long as they are from within the BG).
